---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cambodia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/cambodia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Vietnam for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/vietnam' },
  { title: 'Philippines for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/philippines' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'cambodiaFit', header: 'Cambodia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$280-400/mo', cambodiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$330-470/mo', cambodiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$250-360/mo', cambodiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Pacific Cross', entryAge: '70', renewal: 'To 75', monthlyFrom: '$200-290/mo', cambodiaFit: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'Cambodian Local', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: '$40-100/mo', cambodiaFit: 'Very Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$250-400', annual: '$3,000-4,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$345-530', annual: '$4,140-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$465-710', annual: '$5,580-8,520' },
  { category: 'Cambodia Private Clinic', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: '$20-50/visit' },
  { category: 'Bangkok Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'For serious care' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Cambodia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Cambodia. Angkor Wat, ultra-affordable living, easy visa, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Cambodia"
  subheadline="Cambodia offers Angkor Wat wonder, extremely affordable living, easy long-term visa, and welcoming culture—Southeast Asia most accessible retirement destination with lowest cost of living."
  heroImage="/images/countries/cambodia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Cambodia</h2>
  <p>
    Cambodia offers extraordinary affordability—lowest cost of living in Southeast Asia, easy retirement visa, USD-based economy, and welcoming culture. Angkor Wat is one of the world wonders. For budget-conscious retirees, Cambodia offers unmatched value.
  </p>

  <p>
    Phnom Penh has best services and healthcare. Siem Reap offers Angkor proximity with tourism infrastructure. Sihanoukville and coast offer beach options. Kampot and Kep provide quiet riverside/seaside living. Each area has distinct character and price point.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Bangkok for serious care</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Khmer; English in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $600-1,500/month; extremely affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; hot year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Currency:</strong> USD widely used</li>
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Easy Retirement Visa (ER) available</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Cambodia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Cambodia healthcare is limited—developing country with basic facilities. Phnom Penh has international clinics (Royal Phnom Penh, Sen Sok International) that handle routine care well. Serious conditions require evacuation to Bangkok—3 hours by flight, excellent hospitals.
  </p>

  <p>
    International insurance with Thailand/Bangkok coverage is essential. Many expats routinely use Bangkok for serious healthcare. Local clinics handle minor issues. Plan for medical travel as normal part of health management.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Bangkok Healthcare Hub</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bangkok is the healthcare hub for Cambodia seniors—Bumrungrad, BNH, Bangkok Hospital are world-class and 1-hour flight from Phnom Penh. International insurance must include Thailand coverage. Many expats schedule regular check-ups in Bangkok.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Cambodia has easy visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement Visa (ER)</h3>
  <p>
    For those 55+ with proof of retirement income. One-year multiple-entry visa, renewable. No strict income minimum but typically $1,000+/month demonstrated. Straightforward process through immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-term Business Visa</h3>
  <p>
    E-class visa with extensions—common path for retirees. Buy 12-month business visa (~$300/year) and extend annually. No business required despite name. Flexible and simple.
  </p>

  <h3>Ordinary Visa Extensions</h3>
  <p>
    Tourist visa extendable in-country. Some retirees maintain long-term status through repeated extensions, though ER or E-class is more stable.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Cambodia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa requirement:</strong> None mandatory</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Essential given limited local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Bangkok evacuation:</strong> Critical for serious care</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Thailand must be included</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Cambodia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Asia-Pacific coverage including Thailand is essential. Local healthcare handles routine needs; Bangkok handles serious conditions. Cash payment works for local clinics. Plan for regular Bangkok healthcare visits.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Cambodia, regional coverage with Bangkok access is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Cambodia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia-Pacific network, Bangkok access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Asia expertise, good regional network</li>
    <li><strong>Pacific Cross:</strong> Regional specialist, affordable option</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with Bangkok access essential for Cambodia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Cambodia are moderate given need for regional coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local care is very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Local consultations $20-40; very cheap</li>
    <li><strong>Asia-only coverage:</strong> Regional rather than worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Scheduled Bangkok visits:</strong> Routine care and check-ups</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Budget Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,100/month Social Security. Seeking maximum affordability.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Retirement visa. Cigna Global Asia coverage. Phnom Penh living.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~$320/month. Comfortable living on Social Security alone.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British History Buff, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1,400/month pension. Siem Reap, near Angkor.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Bangkok and UK access. Regular Bangkok check-ups.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~$400/month (~£320). Angkor at doorstep; Bangkok healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Australian Minimalist Couple, Both 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension AUD 2,000/month. Kampot riverside.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Now Health for both. Quiet riverside life; Phnom Penh for clinics.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~$580/month combined (~AUD 860). Extreme affordability; peaceful living.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Cambodia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally yes—stable government, low violent crime. Petty crime exists in tourist areas. Road safety is a concern (chaotic traffic). Cities and tourist areas are safe. Many expats live comfortably with standard precautions. Political situation is stable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Cambodia really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extremely affordable—lowest cost in Southeast Asia. Comfortable retirement possible on $800-1,200/month. Local food very cheap. Rent $200-500 for nice apartment. Domestic help extremely affordable. $1,500/month is comfortable middle-class living.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to use Bangkok for healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For serious conditions, yes. Phnom Penh international clinics handle routine care, minor issues, basic emergencies. Complex care, surgery, specialists require Bangkok. Many expats schedule annual check-ups in Bangkok. Flight is 1 hour, $80-150.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the USD currency useful?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very useful—Cambodia is effectively dollarized. USD accepted everywhere for any transaction. No currency exchange hassle for Americans. ATMs dispense USD. Local riel used for small change only. Simplifies financial life significantly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes with Asia-Pacific coverage essential for Cambodia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Cambodian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
